        `${lastMove?`The rate last moved in ${dateLabel(lastMove.date)}, a ${lastMove.bp<0?'cut':'rise'} of ${Math.abs(lastMove.bp)===25?'a quarter point':Math.abs(lastMove.bp)===50?'half a point':fmt(Math.abs(lastMove.bp)/100,2)+' points'}. `:''}Mortgages, business credit and the peso all reprice off that decision. They reprice first. The rest of the economy follows later.`],
       chart:{title:'Inflation and the policy rate, percent',stat:`${fmt(R.value,2)}%`,series:[line('Headline inflation',inf.slice(-72),GREEN,v=>fmt(v,1)+'%'),line('Policy rate',rateMonthly.slice(-72),INK,v=>fmt(v,2)+'%')],yFormat:v=>fmt(v,1)+'%',band:[2,4],label:'Headline inflation and the Banxico policy rate',srcId:'banxico-inflacion',srcId2:'banxico-tasa-objetivo'}},
      {h2:agree?`Both growth measures agree, and they say slow`:`Two growth numbers disagree, and the slower one is the record`,
       prose:[`The two growth numbers on this page ${agree?'agree':'do not agree'}. The monthly indicator, IGAE, was ${G.value>=0?'up':'down'} <b>${fmt(Math.abs(G.value),1)}%</b> in ${dateLabel(G.date)} from a year earlier. The quarterly national accounts put growth at ${fmt(GDP.value,1)}% for ${quarterLabel(GDP.date)}. ${agree?'Same answer from two directions, so the reading holds.':'Same economy, different answers.'}`,
        `The gap is mostly timing. IGAE lands first, built from partial data, and gets revised afterward. The quarterly figure lands later and settles the record. When the two split, the quarterly one is the number that stands.`],
       chart:{title:'Economic activity, annual percent change by month',stat:`${signed(G.value,1,'%')}`,series:[line('IGAE annual change',igae.slice(-72),GREEN,v=>fmt(v,1)+'%')],yFormat:v=>fmt(v,1)+'%',label:'IGAE annual percentage change by month',srcId:'banxico-igae'}},
      {h2:`The peso trades on rate gaps, not on output`,
       prose:[`The peso answers to interest rates before it answers to growth. A dollar bought <b>${fmt(P.value,2)} pesos</b> on ${shortDate(P.date)}${d3!=null&&Math.abs(d3)>=0.5?`, about ${fmt(Math.abs(d3),1)}% ${pesoWeaker?'more':'less'} than three months before`:''}. What holds the peso up is the difference between peso rates and dollar rates. That difference is what pays a foreign investor to sit in pesos. It shrinks when Banxico cuts.`,
        `A ${pesoWeaker?'weaker':'stronger'} peso works in two directions at once. Imports and dollar debts cost ${pesoWeaker?'more':'less'}. Money sent home from abroad is worth ${pesoWeaker?'more':'less'} when it lands.`],
       chart:{title:'Pesos per US dollar, daily, one year',stat:fmt(P.value,2),series:[line('MXN per USD',peso.slice(-260),GREEN,v=>fmt(v,2))],yFormat:v=>fmt(v,1),label:'Peso per dollar FIX rate, one year',srcId:'banxico-usdmxn-fix'}},
      {h2:`The wage floor is set by decree, not by a market`,
       prose:[`The general minimum wage is <b>MX$${fmt(W.value,2)} a day</b>, set by decree rather than by supply and demand. Adjusted for inflation, it buys roughly ${fmt(Math.abs(RW.value-100),0)}% ${RW.value>=100?'more':'less'} than it did in ${baseYear}. That is a floor, not an average. It says nothing about what a typical worker takes home.`,
        `The floor bites where pay already sits near it. That means formal jobs at or just above the minimum. It also means services whose main cost is labor: kitchens, cleaning, care work. Raise the floor and those prices follow.`],
       chart:{title:`Minimum wage adjusted for prices, ${baseYear} = 100`,stat:fmt(RW.value,0),series:[line('Real minimum wage',real,GREEN,v=>fmt(v,0))],yFormat:v=>fmt(v,0),label:'Inflation-adjusted general minimum wage index',srcId:'banxico-salario-minimo',srcId2:'banxico-inpc'}}
    ],
    updates:changedMatches('economy',3),
    upcoming:eventMatches(/CPI|INPC|IGAE|GDP|Banxico monetary|expectations|employment/i,5),
    sources:[topicSource('banxico-inflacion'),topicSource('banxico-inflacion-subyacente'),topicSource('banxico-tasa-objetivo'),topicSource('banxico-igae'),topicSource('banxico-pib-crecimiento'),topicSource('banxico-usdmxn-fix'),topicSource('banxico-salario-minimo'),topicSource('banxico-inpc')],
    method:'Every reading keeps its own observation date, and direction words are computed from the series, never written by hand. Core inflation is charted on the Numbers page; here it appears once, as a check on the headline.'
  };
